#. <section class="sutta" id="sn35.248"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn35.248:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.248:0.2"
msgid "19. Āsīvisavagga"
msgstr "19. The Simile of the Vipers"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.248:0.3"
msgid "248. Yavakalāpisutta"
msgstr "248. The Sheaf of Barley"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.201"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.248:1.1"
msgid "“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yavakalāpī cātumahāpathe nikkhittā assa."
msgstr "“Mendicants, suppose a sheaf of barley was placed at a crossroads."

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.2"
msgid "Atha cha purisā āgaccheyyuṃ byābhaṅgihatthā."
msgstr "Then six people would come along carrying flails,"

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.3"
msgid "Te yavakalāpiṃ chahi byābhaṅgīhi haneyyuṃ."
msgstr "and started threshing the sheaf of barley."

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.4"
msgid ""
"Evañhi sā, bhikkhave, yavakalāpī suhatā assa chahi byābhaṅgīhi haññamānā."
msgstr ""
"So that sheaf of barley would be thoroughly threshed by those six flails."

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.5"
msgid "Atha sattamo puriso āgaccheyya byābhaṅgihattho."
msgstr "Then a seventh person would come along carrying a flail,"

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.6"
msgid "So taṃ yavakalāpiṃ sattamāya byābhaṅgiyā haneyya."
msgstr "and they’d give the sheaf of barley a seventh threshing."

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.7"
msgid ""
"Evañhi sā bhikkhave, yavakalāpī suhatatarā assa, sattamāya byābhaṅgiyā "
"haññamānā."
msgstr ""
"So that sheaf of barley would be even more thoroughly threshed by that "
"seventh flail."

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.8"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano cakkhusmiṃ haññati "
"manāpāmanāpehi rūpehi … pe …"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, an uneducated ordinary person is struck in the eye by both "
"pleasant and unpleasant sights."

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.9"
msgid "jivhāya haññati manāpāmanāpehi rasehi … pe …"
msgstr "They’re struck in the ear … nose … tongue … body …"

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.10"
msgid "manasmiṃ haññati manāpāmanāpehi dhammehi."
msgstr "mind by both pleasant and unpleasant thoughts."

msgctxt "sn35.248:1.11"
msgid ""
"Sace so, bhikkhave, assutavā puthujjano āyatiṃ punabbhavāya ceteti, evañhi "
"so, bhikkhave, moghapuriso suhatataro hoti, seyyathāpi sā yavakalāpī "
"sattamāya byābhaṅgiyā haññamānā."
msgstr ""
"And if that uneducated ordinary person has intentions regarding rebirth into "
"a new state of existence in the future, that foolish person is even more "
"thoroughly struck, like that sheaf of barley threshed by the seventh person."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.202"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: samupabyūḷho → samupabbūḷho (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "sn35.248:2.1"
msgid "Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, devāsurasaṅgāmo samupabyūḷho ahosi."
msgstr "Once upon a time, a battle was fought between the gods and the demons."

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo asure āmantesi:"
msgstr "Then Vepacitti, lord of demons, addressed the demons:"

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.3"
msgid ""
"‘sace, mārisā, devāsurasaṅgāme samupabyūḷhe asurā jineyyuṃ devā "
"parājineyyuṃ, yena naṃ sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi "
"bandhitvā mama santike āneyyātha asurapuran’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My good sirs, if the demons defeat the gods in this battle, bind Sakka, the "
"lord of gods, by his limbs and neck and bring him to my presence in the "
"castle of demons.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.4"
msgid "Sakkopi kho, bhikkhave, devānamindo deve tāvatiṃse āmantesi:"
msgstr "Meanwhile, Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the gods of the Thirty-Three:"

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.5"
msgid ""
"‘sace, mārisā, devāsurasaṅgāme samupabyūḷhe devā jineyyuṃ asurā "
"parājineyyuṃ, yena naṃ vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi "
"bandhitvā mama santike āneyyātha sudhammaṃ devasabhan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘My good sirs, if the gods defeat the demons in this battle, bind Vepacitti "
"by his limbs and neck and bring him to my presence in the Sudhamma hall of "
"the gods.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.6"
msgid "Tasmiṃ kho pana, bhikkhave, saṅgāme devā jiniṃsu, asurā parājiniṃsu."
msgstr "In that battle the gods won and the demons lost."

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.7"
msgid ""
"Atha kho, bhikkhave, devā tāvatiṃsā vepacittiṃ asurindaṃ kaṇṭhapañcamehi "
"bandhanehi bandhitvā sakkassa devānamindassa santike ānesuṃ sudhammaṃ "
"devasabhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"So the gods of the Thirty-Three bound Vepacitti by his limbs and neck and "
"brought him to Sakka’s presence in the Sudhamma hall of the gods."

#. VAR: baddho → bandho (si, s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.248:2.8"
msgid ""
"Tatra sudaṃ, bhikkhave, vepacitti asurindo kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi baddho "
"hoti."
msgstr "And there Vepacitti remained bound by his limbs and neck"

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.9"
msgid "Yadā kho, bhikkhave, vepacittissa asurindassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "until he had this thought:"

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.10"
msgid ""
"‘dhammikā kho devā, adhammikā asurā, idheva dānāhaṃ devapuraṃ gacchāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s the gods who are principled, while the demons are unprincipled. Now I "
"belong right here in the castle of the gods.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.11"
msgid ""
"Atha kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi muttaṃ attānaṃ samanupassati, dibbehi ca "
"pañcahi kāmaguṇehi samappito samaṅgībhūto paricāreti."
msgstr ""
"Then he found himself freed from the bonds on his limbs and neck, and "
"entertained himself, supplied and provided with the five kinds of heavenly "
"sensual stimulation."

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.12"
msgid "Yadā ca kho, bhikkhave, vepacittissa asurindassa evaṃ hoti:"
msgstr "But when he had this thought:"

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.13"
msgid ""
"‘dhammikā kho asurā, adhammikā devā, tattheva dānāhaṃ asurapuraṃ "
"gamissāmī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘It’s the demons who are principled, while the gods are unprincipled. Now I "
"will go over there to the castle of the demons.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.14"
msgid ""
"atha kaṇṭhapañcamehi bandhanehi baddhaṃ attānaṃ samanupassati, dibbehi ca "
"pañcahi kāmaguṇehi parihāyati."
msgstr ""
"Then he found himself bound by his limbs and neck, and the five kinds of "
"heavenly sensual stimulation disappeared."

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.15"
msgid "Evaṃ sukhumaṃ kho, bhikkhave, vepacittibandhanaṃ."
msgstr "That’s how subtly Vepacitti was bound."

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.16"
msgid "Tato sukhumataraṃ mārabandhanaṃ."
msgstr "But the bonds of Māra are even more subtle than that."

msgctxt "sn35.248:2.17"
msgid "Maññamāno kho, bhikkhave, baddho mārassa, amaññamāno mutto pāpimato."
msgstr ""
"When you have conceit, you’re bound by Māra. Not conceiving, you’re free "
"from the Wicked One."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.248:3.1"
msgid ""
"‘Asmī’ti, bhikkhave, maññitametaṃ, ‘ayamahamasmī’ti maññitametaṃ, ‘bhavissan’"
"ti maññitametaṃ, ‘na bhavissan’ti maññitametaṃ, ‘rūpī bhavissan’ti "
"maññitametaṃ, ‘arūpī bhavissan’ti maññitametaṃ, ‘saññī bhavissan’ti "
"maññitametaṃ, ‘asaññī bhavissan’ti maññitametaṃ, ‘nevasaññīnāsaññī bhavissan’"
"ti maññitametaṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are all forms of conceiving: ‘I am’, ‘I am this’, ‘I will be’, ‘I will "
"not be’, ‘I will have form’, ‘I will be formless’, ‘I will be percipient’, ‘"
"I will be non-percipient’, ‘I will be neither percipient nor non-percipient.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:3.2"
msgid "Maññitaṃ, bhikkhave, rogo, maññitaṃ gaṇḍo, maññitaṃ sallaṃ."
msgstr "Conceit is a disease, a boil, a dart."

#. VAR: amaññamānena → amaññitamānena (pts1, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.248:3.3"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘amaññamānena cetasā viharissāmā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"So mendicants, you should train yourselves like this: ‘We will live with a "
"heart that does not conceive.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:3.4"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.203"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.248:4.1"
msgid ""
"‘Asmī’ti, bhikkhave, iñjitametaṃ, ‘ayamahamasmī’ti iñjitametaṃ, ‘bhavissan’"
"ti iñjitametaṃ, ‘na bhavissan’ti iñjitametaṃ, ‘rūpī bhavissan’ti "
"iñjitametaṃ, ‘arūpī bhavissan’ti iñjitametaṃ, ‘saññī bhavissan’ti "
"iñjitametaṃ, ‘asaññī bhavissan’ti iñjitametaṃ, ‘nevasaññīnāsaññī bhavissan’"
"ti iñjitametaṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are all disturbances: ‘I am’, ‘I am this’, ‘I will be’, ‘I will not be’"
", ‘I will have form’, ‘I will be formless’, ‘I will be percipient’, ‘I will "
"be non-percipient’, ‘I will be neither percipient nor non-percipient.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:4.2"
msgid "Iñjitaṃ, bhikkhave, rogo, iñjitaṃ gaṇḍo, iñjitaṃ sallaṃ."
msgstr "Disturbances are a disease, a boil, a dart."

#. VAR: aniñjamānena → aniñjiyamānena (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.248:4.3"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘aniñjamānena cetasā viharissāmā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"So mendicants, you should train yourselves like this: ‘We will live with a "
"heart free of disturbances.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:4.4"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

# At SN 45.7, injita and phandita are used together in the sense of “movement, shaking, trembling” (of the body and mind)
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.248:5.1"
msgid ""
"‘Asmī’ti, bhikkhave, phanditametaṃ, ‘ayamahamasmī’ti phanditametaṃ, "
"‘bhavissan’ti … pe … ‘na bhavissan’ti … ‘rūpī bhavissan’ti … ‘arūpī "
"bhavissan’ti … ‘saññī bhavissan’ti … ‘asaññī bhavissan’ti … ‘"
"nevasaññīnāsaññī bhavissan’ti phanditametaṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are all tremblings: ‘I am’, ‘I am this’, ‘I will be’, ‘I will not be’, "
"‘I will have form’, ‘I will be formless’, ‘I will be percipient’, ‘I will be "
"non-percipient’, ‘I will be neither percipient nor non-percipient.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:5.2"
msgid "Phanditaṃ, bhikkhave, rogo, phanditaṃ gaṇḍo, phanditaṃ sallaṃ."
msgstr "Trembling is a disease, a boil, a dart."

#. VAR: aphandamānena → aphandiyamānena (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "sn35.248:5.3"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘aphandamānena cetasā viharissāmā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"So mendicants, you should train yourselves like this: ‘We will live with a "
"heart free of tremblings.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:5.4"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.248:6.1"
msgid ""
"‘Asmī’ti, bhikkhave, papañcitametaṃ, ‘ayamahamasmī’ti papañcitametaṃ, "
"‘bhavissan’ti … pe … ‘na bhavissan’ti … ‘rūpī bhavissan’ti … ‘arūpī "
"bhavissan’ti … ‘saññī bhavissan’ti … ‘asaññī bhavissan’ti … ‘"
"nevasaññīnāsaññī bhavissan’ti papañcitametaṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are all proliferations: ‘I am’, ‘I am this’, ‘I will be’, ‘I will not "
"be’, ‘I will have form’, ‘I will be formless’, ‘I will be percipient’, ‘I "
"will be non-percipient’, ‘I will be neither percipient nor non-percipient.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:6.2"
msgid "Papañcitaṃ, bhikkhave, rogo, papañcitaṃ gaṇḍo, papañcitaṃ sallaṃ."
msgstr "Proliferation is a disease, a boil, a dart."

msgctxt "sn35.248:6.3"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘nippapañcena cetasā viharissāmā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"So mendicants, you should train yourselves like this: ‘We will live with a "
"heart free of proliferation.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:6.4"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabbaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.248:7.1"
msgid ""
"‘Asmī’ti, bhikkhave, mānagatametaṃ, ‘ayamahamasmī’ti mānagatametaṃ, "
"‘bhavissan’ti mānagatametaṃ, ‘na bhavissan’ti mānagatametaṃ, ‘rūpī bhavissan’"
"ti mānagatametaṃ, ‘arūpī bhavissan’ti mānagatametaṃ, ‘saññī bhavissan’ti "
"mānagatametaṃ, ‘asaññī bhavissan’ti mānagatametaṃ, ‘nevasaññīnāsaññī "
"bhavissan’ti mānagatametaṃ."
msgstr ""
"These are all conceits: ‘I am’, ‘I am this’, ‘I will be’, ‘I will not be’, ‘"
"I will have form’, ‘I will be formless’, ‘I will be percipient’, ‘I will be "
"non-percipient’, ‘I will be neither percipient nor non-percipient.’"

msgctxt "sn35.248:7.2"
msgid "Mānagataṃ, bhikkhave, rogo, mānagataṃ gaṇḍo, mānagataṃ sallaṃ."
msgstr "Conceit is a disease, a boil, a dart."

msgctxt "sn35.248:7.3"
msgid "Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘nihatamānena cetasā viharissāmā’ti—"
msgstr ""
"So mendicants, you should train yourselves like this: ‘We will live with a "
"heart that has struck down conceit.’”"

msgctxt "sn35.248:7.4"
msgid "evañhi vo, bhikkhave, sikkhitabban”ti."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.248:7.5"
msgid "Ekādasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.248:7.6"
msgid "Āsīvisavaggo catuttho."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.204"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.248:8.1"
msgid "Āsīviso ratho kummo,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.248:8.2"
msgid "dve dārukkhandhā avassuto;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.248:8.3"
msgid "Dukkhadhammā kiṃsukā vīṇā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.248:8.4"
msgid "chappāṇā yavakalāpīti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.248:8.5"
msgid "Saḷāyatanavagge catutthapaṇṇāsako samatto."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="vagguddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "sn35.248:9.1"
msgid "Nandikkhayo saṭṭhinayo,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.248:9.2"
msgid "samuddo uragena ca;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.248:9.3"
msgid "Catupaṇṇāsakā ete,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn35.248:9.4"
msgid "nipātesu pakāsitāti."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn35.248:9.5"
msgid "Saḷāyatanasaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on the six sense fields are complete."
